In this paper, a lab automation drone concept is introduced. Here, a robotic limb is attached to a robotic rotorcraft. The limb's gripper allows the unmanned aerial vehicle to manipulate objects such as micro-arrays and test tubes often used in high-speed systems. The resulting drone could augment existing systems. The 6-axis robotic arm and gripper design are presented. Test-and-evaluation approach and results are also given.
